---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { parish } from '../../parish.config';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn about Byzantine Catholicism and our parish community.">
  <section class="page-header page-header--icon">
    <div class="container content-width text-center">
      <h1>About Our Parish</h1>
      <p class="page-header__subtitle">
        An ancient faith you probably didn't know existed â︎ and a community that's been 
        keeping it alive for generations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">

      <!-- What is Byzantine Catholicism -->
      <h2>What is Byzantine Catholicism?</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider gold-divider--left" />

      <p>
        Here's something most Catholics don't know: the Catholic Church has never been just 
        Roman. There are 23 Eastern Catholic Churches â︎ all in full communion with the Pope, 
        all fully Catholic â︎ that worship in traditions far older than what you'll find in 
        most parishes in North America.
      </p>
      <p>
        The <strong>Byzantine rite</strong> is one of those traditions. It traces its roots to 
        the early Church in Constantinople and the great Fathers â︎ St. John Chrysostom, 
        St. Basil the Great, the Desert Fathers. If you've ever felt like there must be 
        <em>more</em> to Christian worship than what you've experienced, you might be right. 
        The Eastern tradition has been preserving that "more" for 1,500 years.
      </p>
      <p>
        St. John Paul II wrote that the Church must "breathe with both lungs" â︎ Western and 
        Eastern. Most Catholics have only ever breathed with one. Byzantine Catholicism is 
        the other lung, and it changes everything about how you experience the faith.
      </p>

      <div class="cross-ornament">â︎︎ ︎ â︎︎ ︎ â︎︎ ︎</div>

      <!-- How We're Different -->
      <h2>How Our Worship Differs</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider gold-divider--left" />

      <div class="comparison">
        <div class="comparison__item">
          <h4>🎵 Liturgy</h4>
          <p>
            Our Divine Liturgy is almost entirely <strong>sung</strong>. The prayers themselves are 
            the music â︎ there are no hymns inserted between parts. The entire service is one 
            continuous act of worship.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="comparison__item comparison__item--featured">
          <h4>🖼️ Icons</h4>
          <p>
            Sacred icons are central to our worship â︎ they are windows into heaven, not mere 
            decoration. The <strong>iconostasis</strong> (icon screen) before the altar is the 
            defining architectural feature of a Byzantine church.
          </p>
          <img src="/images/iconostasis.jpg" alt="Golden iconostasis" class="comparison__img" />
        </div>
        <div class="comparison__item">
          <h4>🍞 Communion</h4>
          <p>
            We receive the Body and Blood of Christ together, from a spoon, in 
            <strong>leavened bread</strong>. Infants receive Communion from the day of their baptism.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="comparison__item">
          <h4>👶 Sacraments of Initiation</h4>
          <p>
            Baptism, Chrismation (Confirmation), and first Communion are all given together â︎ even 
            to infants. A child is fully initiated into the Church from the very beginning.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="comparison__item">
          <h4>💍 Married Clergy</h4>
          <p>
            In the Byzantine tradition, married men may be ordained to the priesthood. Many of our 
            priests are married with families. Bishops are drawn from the monastic ranks.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="comparison__item">
          <h4>📅 The Calendar</h4>
          <p>
            We follow the liturgical calendar of the Eastern Church, with its own cycle of feasts, 
            fasts, and seasons. Some dates differ from the Roman calendar â︎ notably, we follow the 
            Julian calendar for some celebrations.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cross-ornament">â︎︎ ︎ â︎︎ ︎ â︎︎ ︎</div>

      <!-- Our Parish -->
      <h2>Our Parish</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider gold-divider--left" />

      <p>
        Our parish is named for the <strong>Dormition</strong> â︎ the "falling asleep" of the 
        Blessed Virgin Mary, one of the great feasts of the Eastern Church. It's a fitting name: 
        the Dormition is not a story of loss, but of passage â︎ the Theotokos entering fully 
        into the life she was created for.
      </p>
      <p>
        Dormition parish has served the Ukrainian Catholic community in west Edmonton for 
        generations. But increasingly, our pews include people from all backgrounds â︎ 
        Roman Catholics drawn to the Eastern tradition, converts from Protestantism and 
        Orthodoxy, seekers who walked in one Sunday and never left. If that sounds like 
        it might be you, you're in good company.
      </p>
      <p>
        We celebrate Divine Liturgy in both English and Ukrainian. You don't need to be 
        Ukrainian. You don't need to know the prayers. You just need to come.
      </p>

      {parish.pastor && (
        <div class="pastor-card" id="pastor">
          <div class="pastor-card__info">
            <h3>Our Pastor</h3>
            <p class="pastor-card__name">{parish.pastor.title} {parish.pastor.name}</p>
            <p class="pastor-card__role">{parish.pastor.role}</p>
            <p>
              For sacramental preparation, spiritual direction, or any questions about the parish 
              or the faith, please contact Father directly at 
              <a href={`tel:${parish.phone}`}>{parish.phone}</a> or 
              <a href={`mailto:${parish.email}`}>{parish.email}</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      )}

      <div class="cross-ornament">â︎︎ ︎ â︎︎ ︎ â︎︎ ︎</div>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <div id="contact">
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <hr class="gold-divider gold-divider--left" />

        <div class="contact-grid">
          <div class="contact-item">
            <h4>📍 Address</h4>
            <p>
              {parish.address.street}<br />
              {parish.address.city}, {parish.address.province} {parish.address.postalCode}
            </p>
            <a href={parish.address.mapUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn--outline" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">
              Get Directions â︎
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="contact-item">
            <h4>📞 Phone & Email</h4>
            <p>
              <a href={`tel:${parish.phone}`}>{parish.phone}</a><br />
              <a href={`mailto:${parish.email}`}>{parish.email}</a>
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="contact-item">
            <h4>🕐 Office Hours</h4>
            <p>
              By appointment. Please call or email to arrange a visit with Father.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-dark), var(--color-primary));
    color: var(--color-text-inverse);
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    color: var(--color-text-inverse);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-header__subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: rgba(250, 246, 239, 0.8);
    max-width: 55ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .comparison {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .comparison__item {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .comparison__item h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .comparison__item p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .comparison__img {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    max-height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .comparison__item--featured {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  @media (min-width: 769px) {
    .comparison__item--featured {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-xl);
      align-items: center;
    }
    .comparison__item--featured .comparison__img {
      max-height: 250px;
      grid-row: 1 / 3;
      grid-column: 2;
    }
  }

  .pastor-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .pastor-card__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .pastor-card__role {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .contact-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .contact-item {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .contact-item h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
</style>
